        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> Well, I went to HS last night for the first time, and the exp there is quite good. I zoned in, charmed a skelly wanderer, then sicced it on his buddy, the other wanderer. Hit CoS, and root dotted my former pet. Heh, was fun. Then I root-cooked the golems for awhile. Kinda boring, but not bad AA exp. </P><P>Anyway, a friend needed help, so I camped in the center of the room. This wasn't the best idea...I zoned back in and took 2 HT's. I ended up running off the ledge and gating. Strange, when I zoned in, neither of the wanderers saw me. I guess you have to be in that perfect zone-in spot....</P><P>Anyway, while I was floating down, I noticed a lot of undead mobs in the basement area. Just wondering if this is a viable source of exp? Either root-cook or pet-tank/slow the mobs? I might try this tomorrow night if I get the chance...just looking for some tips so I don't die right off the bat =)</P><P>Tombfyre Cryptwalker<BR>Warlock of Luclin</font></td>

