         Soloing basement is quite doable.. if I solo HS that's usually where I go.</P><P>Here's an old thread that proves some of it. ;)</P><P><a href="http://necro.eqclasses.com/forums/topic.asp?TOPIC_ID=5132" target="_blank">http://necro.eqclasses.com/forums/topic.asp?TOPIC_ID=5132</a></P><P>I'd solo the side without the golems first (think it's the west halls). For one it has more spawns, and secondly more undeads. Use the same strategy you used at zone in.. charm a skelly, have it kill something, then kill your pet.</P><P>The pulls are conveniently set up so that unless you miss respawn or catch a wanderer, you'll always have single pulls as long as your charm sticks.</P><P><BR><a href="http://tru7h.org/absor/" target="_blank">http://tru7h.org/absor/</a> -  ask absor anything!<BR><a href="http://xzzy.org/ereet/" target="_blank">http://xzzy.org/ereet/</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
